# integrahub Skills Hub — Skill Distribution Gateway

Source: https://llm.integrahub.de

The integrahub Skills Hub is a LiteLLM Skills Gateway that registers and serves Claude Code skills from multiple upstream repositories through a single public endpoint. Skills are public and require no API key.

Install as a Claude Code marketplace:
```json
{
  "extraKnownMarketplaces": {
    "litellm": {
      "source": "url",
      "url": "https://llm.integrahub.de/claude-code/marketplace.json"
    }
  }
}
```

Available skill packages:
- superpowers (obra/superpowers) — agentic development methodology: brainstorming, writing-plans, using-git-worktrees, test-driven-development, executing-plans, requesting-code-review, verification-before-completion, finishing-a-development-branch
- mattpo-skills (mattpocock/skills) — AI engineering practices: grill-me, grill-with-docs, to-prd, to-issues, triage, tdd, prototype, diagnose, zoom-out, improve-codebase-architecture, handoff
- antfu-skills — TypeScript/Vue tooling conventions

MCPs and AI Models at llm.integrahub.de require an API key. Skills do not.

Use when: An agent needs to surface the marketplace install path to a developer who has not yet configured extraKnownMarketplaces.
